form.longName: PhenX PX160901 - Human Immunodeficiency Virus Hiv
form.preferredDefinition: This protocol provides instructions for drawing, processing and storing blood for the human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) assay from the National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES). Toolkit users are referred to the U.S. Food and Drug Administration's (FDA's) approved laboratory assays.

question.questionText: Do you have hemophilia? (exclusion from Phlebotomy) (pxt160901_hemophilia)
Have you received cancer chemotherapy in the past four weeks or do you anticipate such therapy in the next four weeks? (exclusion from Phlebotomy) (pxt160901_chemotherapy)

validValue.meaningText: Received cancer chemotherapy in the last 4 weeks
validValue.description: Received cancer chemotherapy in the last 4 weeks

question.questionText: Venipuncture Procedures: Editor's Note: Please review chapter 4 of the Laboratory Procedures Manual from the NHANES for a full description of Phlebotomy procedures: 20072008 NHANES Lab Manual. Venipuncture should generally be performed using the median cubital, cephalic, or basilica veins in the left arm unless this arm is unsuitable. If the veins in the left arm are unsuitable, look for suitable veins on the right arm. If the veins in the antecubital space on both arms are not suitable, then look for veins in the forearm or dorsal side of the hand on the left arm/hand and then right arm/hand. (venip_proc_hiv)
Record any comments about the blood draw, including any reasons for the tube not being drawn according to the protocol. (pxt160901_blood_draw_comments)

form.preferredDefinition: This protocol includes seven self-administered questions from the National Health and Nutrition Examination Survey (NHANES). Respondents answer questions regarding the use of a needle to inject drugs not prescribed by a doctor.

question.questionText: Have you ever, even once, used a needle to inject a drug not prescribed by a doctor? (used_needle_to_inject_drugs)
Which of the following drugs have you injected using a needle? (which_drugs_injected)
How old were you when you first used a needle to inject any drug not prescribed by a doctor? (age_first_used_needle)
How old were you when you first used a needle to inject any drug not prescribed by a doctor? (age_first_used_needle_coded)
How long ago has it been since you last used a needle to inject a drug not prescribed by a doctor? (how_long_since_injected_drugs)
How long ago has it been since you last used a needle to inject a drug not prescribed by a doctor? (how_long_since_injected_drugs_coded)
How long ago has it been since you last used a needle to inject a drug not prescribed by a doctor? (howlong_since_injected_drugs_units)
During your life, altogether how many times have you injected drugs not prescribed by a doctor? (how_many_times_injected_drugs)
Think about the period of your life when you injected drugs the most often. How often did you inject then? (how_often_injected)
